* ============================================================
*  Student self-registering FUNCTION liveness proof
*
*  Purpose: confirm at RUNTIME that the self-registering student
*  expression functions in src/ext/fn/fn_student_text_autoreg.cpp
*  are actually registered (static-init AutoRegister fired) and
*  callable through the expression engine.
*
*  Source-level evidence already established: the TU is pulled into
*  the dottalkpp executable by the src/CMakeLists.txt GLOB_RECURSE
*  (src/ext is NOT in _EXCLUDE_DIRS), so the static initializer runs.
*  This script is the runtime confirmation.
*
*  Expected output:
*    STU_UPPER("abc")     -> ABC
*    STU_REPEAT("ab", 3)  -> ababab
*  If instead you see "Unknown function" or an empty/echoed name,
*  the self-registration did NOT fire (report it).
*
*  RUN (host, after building):
*    ./datarun --script dottalkpp/data/scripts/ext/stu_functions_liveness.dts
* ============================================================
SET TALK ON

* --- STU_UPPER: 1-arg uppercase ---
? STU_UPPER("abc")

* --- STU_REPEAT: 2-arg repeat ---
? STU_REPEAT("ab", 3)

* --- negative/edge behavior (documents the contract) ---
? STU_REPEAT("x", 0)

ECHO ============================================================
ECHO STU FUNCTION LIVENESS: expect ABC, then ababab, then empty line.
ECHO ============================================================
